bug.description:
gstbasesrc.h says:
@create: Ask the subclass to create a buffer with offset and size. When the subclass returns GST_FLOW_OK, it MUST return a buffer of the requested size unless fewer bytes are available because an EOS condition is near.
Thus, the size value is critical for the behavior of create callback. However, the current implementation of create callback of SRC_IIO does NOT use size at all. If it is ok because this callback is never invoked, add assert(0); so that we can ensure it.
